      "text": "Question 3: We have 8 same looking\ncoins, out of which, 7 weigh the\nsame. And one coin is slighltly lesser.\nYou're only given a weighing scale.\nHow do you find out which coin is\nthe odd one out, and in the least\nnumber of comparisons.",
