      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782151721027,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Question 4: You are asked to find the highest\nfloor of a 100-story building from which an egg\ncan be dropped without breaking. You have two\neggs to test-drop from the building, you can\ncontinue to drop your eggs until they break.\n\n- If the egg doesn't break at a certain floor,\nit will not break at any floor below.\n- If the eggs break at a certain floor, it will\nbreak on all the floors above.\n- The egg may break on the first floor\n- The egg may break on the second floor.",
      "fontSize": 59.71547293593684,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Question 4: You are asked to find the highest floor of a 100-story building from which an egg can be dropped without breaking. You have two eggs to test-drop from the building, you can continue to drop your eggs until they break.\n\n- If the egg doesn't break at a certain floor, it will not break at any floor below.\n- If the eggs break at a certain floor, it will break on all the floors above.\n- The egg may break on the first floor\n- The egg may break on the second floor.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
